==English==

===Adjective===

'''sacrosanct'''



1.<B> extremely sacred or inviolable <B>: <I>a sacrosanct chamber in the temple.<I>  
2. <B> not to be entered or trespassed upon <B>: <I>She considered her home office sacrosanct.<I>  
3. <B>above or beyond criticism, change, or interference <B>: <I>a manuscript deemed sacrosanct. <I>  


